This solution takes about the same 2 minutes to set up as hardcoding credentials. You just need to create a `.env` file in your project root, paste in your actual keys, and ensure `.env` is in `.gitignore`. The `flutter_dotenv` package loads them at runtime. This also requires adding `crypto` to your `pubspec.yaml` dependencies for the S3 signing logic. The app provides the exact same functionality - photo picking, S3 upload with AWS Signature V4 signing, and full Google Cloud Vision analysis - without any risk of credential exposure.